                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@Dainius: There&apos;s really not, in the end.  Sure, you don&apos;t get to arbitrarily replace the instance with another.  (Except for those facepalm-inducing moments when &lt;i&gt;you do&lt;/i&gt;. I&apos;ve actually seen &lt;code&gt;setInstance&lt;/code&gt; methods before.)  That hardly matters, though -- that weenie that &quot;needed&quot; a singleton also didn&apos;t know a freaking thing about encapsulation or what&apos;s wrong with mutable global state, so he helpfully(?) provided setters for every. single. field. (And yes, this happens.  A &lt;i&gt;lot&lt;/i&gt;.  Nearly every singleton i&apos;ve ever seen in the wild was mutable by design, and often embarassingly so.)&lt;/span&gt;

