            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Lest we talk past each other, i&apos;m not just talking about a globally available instance.  There are plenty of cases for that.  What i&apos;m talking about (particularly when i say &quot;capital-S Singleton&quot;) is the GoF&apos;s Singleton pattern, which embeds that single global instance in the class itself, exposes it via a &lt;code&gt;getInstance&lt;/code&gt; or similarly named method, and prevents the existence of a second instance.  Frankly, at that point, you might as well not even have the &lt;i&gt;one&lt;/i&gt; instance.&lt;/span&gt;

