                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;1.  All those hidden dependencies?  &lt;i&gt;Those are bad too.&lt;/i&gt;  Hidden dependencies are always evil. But in the case of the CRT and OS, they&apos;re already there, and they&apos;re the only way to get something done.  (Try writing a C program without using the runtime or OS.)  That ability to do stuff vastly outweighs their negatives.  Singletons in our code don&apos;t get that luxury; since they&apos;re firmly within our sphere of control and responsibility, every usage (read: every additional hidden dependency) should be justifiable as the only reasonable way to get stuff done.  Very, &lt;i&gt;very&lt;/i&gt; few of them actually are.&lt;/span&gt;

